values:
I was just told by Healer Goodensnake that Theo will wake. 



It may be a while yet. But he will wake. A full recovery is expected within reasonable time.

I have to go to Italy for a few days. Alcimar requires me to attend a critical conference and it would appear that nothing up to and including my own untimely demise constitutes an excuse for absence. 



<s>There is nothing I can do here regardless.</s>

Theo has been attacked. He is badly injured and in Sct. Mungo's. 



Millie and Draco, you are closer - can one or both of you please go there until I can come?

I am leaving for London shortly. Alone, for now, though I suspect Jaspar grows tired of never seeing Alcimar face to face. English officials always seemed like either debauched vicars or grey mice to me when I was a child, and but for a few notable exceptions this has not changed. I've yet to decide which category Jaspar fits into, though I am swayed towards the former by the scandalous looks he is always throwing me when I show up for meetings. It seems entirely lost on him that Brazilian wizarding fashion does not endorse neck-to-floor coveradge, especially not for official representatives of o Ministerio. Not so with Natia when she accompanies me. It would seem Jaspar is of an inclination to appreciate beauty only in the fairer sex. I am sorely tempted to ask the hapless specimen to have lunch with me and ask Draco to join us. The spectacle of unbridled sensual come-hither from such a beautiful man may just shake Jaspar out of his perpetual frowning stupor, and afford me no small amusement. Regardless, I shall perhaps stop by the Manor if I find the time between meetings. I seem to fail at the art of politely announcing my arrival in a timely fashion when it comes to private encounters. However, even if Draco is not there, Narcissa is always pleasant company. And tonight I shall see a friend thought long lost. And dreaming, as it were, held brotherly speech With one whose thought I had not hoped to reach.
